---
import MainLayout from '../../layouts/MainLayout.astro';
import tailimPhoto from '../../assets/attorneys/tailim.jpg';
---

<MainLayout title="Tailim Song | Managing Partner">
  <section class="space-y-10">
    <div class="grid gap-8 lg:grid-cols-[320px_1fr]">
      <aside class="space-y-4 rounded-3xl border border-slate-200 bg-white p-6 text-center shadow-sm">
        <div class="overflow-hidden rounded-2xl bg-white">
          <img src={tailimPhoto.src} alt="Tailim Song" class="block h-auto w-full rounded-2xl" />
        </div>
        <div class="space-y-1">
          <h1 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-slate-900">Tailim Song</h1>
          <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-slate-600">Managing Partner</p>
        </div>
        <div class="rounded-2xl bg-white p-4 text-left">
          <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-slate-900">Contact</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-slate-700">
            Email: <a href="mailto:tsong@songwhiddon.com" class="underline decoration-slate-300 hover:decoration-slate-500">tsong@songwhiddon.com</a>
          </p>
          <p class="text-sm text-slate-700">
            Phone: <a href="tel:+12145288400" class="underline decoration-slate-300 hover:decoration-slate-500">(214) 528-8400</a>
          </p>
          <p class="text-sm text-slate-700">
            Fax: <a href="tel:+12145288402" class="underline decoration-slate-300 hover:decoration-slate-500">(214) 528-8402</a>
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="rounded-2xl bg-white p-4 text-left">
          <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-slate-900">Practices</p>
          <ul class="mt-2 space-y-1 text-sm text-slate-700">
            <li>Civil litigation</li>
            <li>Commercial transactions</li>
            <li>Business disputes</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="rounded-2xl bg-white p-4 space-y-3 text-left">
          <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-slate-900">Courts of admittance</p>
          <div>
            <p class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-slate-600">Federal</p>
            <ul class="mt-2 space-y-1 text-sm text-slate-700">
              <li>Second Circuit Court of Appeals</li>
              <li>Fifth Circuit Court of Appeals</li>
              <li>Sixth Circuit Court of Appeals</li>
              <li>Texas Northern District Court</li>
              <li>Texas Eastern District Court</li>
              <li>Texas Southern District Court</li>
              <li>Texas Western District Court</li>
              <li>California Central District Court</li>
              <li>California Eastern District Court</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div>
            <p class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-slate-600">State</p>
            <ul class="mt-2 space-y-1 text-sm text-slate-700">
              <li>
                California, 1993 —
                <a href="https://apps.calbar.ca.gov/attorney/Licensee/Detail/169048" class="underline decoration-slate-300 hover:decoration-slate-500" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">profile</a>
              </li>
              <li>
                Texas, 1995 —
                <a href="https://www.texasbar.com/attorneys/member.cfm?id=155141" class="underline decoration-slate-300 hover:decoration-slate-500" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">profile</a>
              </li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="rounded-2xl bg-white p-4 text-left">
          <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-slate-900">Education</p>
          <ul class="mt-2 space-y-1 text-sm text-slate-700">
            <li>Southwestern University School of Law, Los Angeles, California</li>
            <li>University of Texas, Austin, Texas</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </aside>

      <article class="space-y-8 rounded-3xl border border-slate-200 bg-white p-6 shadow-sm md:p-8">
        <div class="space-y-3">
          <p class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.25em] text-slate-500">Profile</p>
          <p class="text-lg text-slate-700">
            Founder of Song Whiddon, PLLC, Tailim leads complex litigation and advisory matters with nearly three decades of experience
            across federal and state courts. He serves businesses and individuals in Texas and California, pairing courtroom focus with
            practical business judgment.
          </p>
          <p class="text-lg text-slate-700">
            Tailim attended Southwestern University School of Law in Los Angeles, where he was Vice Justice for the Phi Alpha Delta Law
            Fraternity International, President of the Environmental Law Forum, and a member of the International Law Society. Before law
            school, he attended the University of Texas at Austin.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="space-y-3">
          <p class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.25em] text-slate-500">Industry experience</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-slate-700">Representative areas served:</p>
          <ul class="grid grid-cols-2 gap-x-8 gap-y-2 text-sm text-slate-700 sm:grid-cols-3">
            <li>Litigation</li>
            <li>Real estate</li>
            <li>Land-use</li>
            <li>Zoning</li>
            <li>Manufacturing</li>
            <li>Intellectual property</li>
            <li>Technology</li>
            <li>Finance</li>
            <li>Labor</li>
            <li>Securities</li>
            <li>Environmental</li>
            <li>Aviation</li>
            <li>Consumer products</li>
            <li>Insurance</li>
            <li>Entertainment</li>
            <li>Transportation</li>
            <li>Medical devices</li>
            <li>Oil and gas</li>
            <li>Renewable energy</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="space-y-3">
          <p class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.25em] text-slate-500">Associations</p>
          <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm text-slate-700">
            <li>Dallas Bar Association, Member</li>
            <li>Asian American Bar Association, Member</li>
            <li>Dallas Asian American Cultural Center, Friends' Committee, Member</li>
            <li>Cultural Affairs Commission, City of Dallas, Former Commissioner</li>
            <li>Dallas Asian-American Bar Association, Former Vice President</li>
            <li>Dallas Asian-American Bar Association, Director</li>
            <li>State Bar of Texas, Texas Minority Counsel Program, Former Director</li>
            <li>Asian District Development Association of Dallas, Former Chairman</li>
            <li>Steering Committee for Dallas Asian American Cultural Center, Former Member</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="space-y-3">
          <p class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.25em] text-slate-500">Publications</p>
          <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm text-slate-700">
            <li>
              Co-author of chapter:
              <span class="italic">"The Duties of Confidentiality and the Attorney-Client Privilege in the Context of the Prospective Client"</span>,
              published by the American Bar Association in <em>The Attorney-Client Privilege in Civil Litigation: Protecting and Defending Confidentiality</em>.
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>

      </article>
    </div>
  </section>
</MainLayout>
